posts.title: MAGA Monday: The future we want is ALWAYS outside of our comfort zones
posts.content:
Today is perhaps the most MAGA Monday in the history of our movement.

Victory is within reach if we ignore the psy-ops and get everyone out to Vote for Donald J. Trump.

Take a risk by reaching out to someone and ask that they vote for Trump. Our future depends on it.

If they say yes drive them to the polls. If they say no, thank them for listening and move on to the next.

It could be a friend, a relative, or even someone you’re interested in romantically. No matter what make it a date, and VOTE, VOTE, VOTE!

This Monday will only happen once in our lifetime, make it count!

Find Early Voting and Election Day poll locations: https://www.usa.gov/state-election-office

Volunteer to door knock and more for Trump. (Install the app) https://swampthevoteusa.com

posts.title: Soros-Funded 'Fake News' Network's $9 Million Digital Ad Blitz under the guise of local "news" outlets.
posts.author: rdvs34283

link_metadata.description: Over the past three months, an avowed left-wing organization has spent more than $9 million on Facebook ads boosting Vice President Kamala Harris and attacking former president Donald Trump. The spots have reached scores of swing state voters using a Facebook feature that allows advertisers to submit their own data—for political groups, that is, data they've compiled on voters—to reach a precise audience.  The practice is considered standard operating procedure for campaigns and PACs. But the group behind the $9 million digital ad blitz is neither a campaign nor a PAC—at least not on paper. Instead, it's Courier Newsroom, liberal operative Tara McGowan's organization that pushes Democratic talking points under the guise of local "news" outlets.
link_metadata.title: 'They're Targeting Voters Under the Guise of a News Org': Inside a Soros-Funded 'Fake News' Network's $9 Million Digital Ad Blitz
